\p
\v 5 The reasonВҰ139951 that I asked you to stay behindВҰ139952 in CreteВҰ139957 was so that you would find what needed to be reorganised and so that you would appointВҰ139965 eldersВҰ139968 in every cityВҰ139967 just as I had directedВҰ139972 you.
\v 6 \x + \xo 1:6-9: \xt 1Tim 3:2-7.\x*Each elder must have a clean record, be the husbandВҰ139979 of one wifeВҰ139978, and have believingВҰ139982 childrenВҰ139980 who are not wild or disobedient.
\v 7 Any overseerВҰ139992 \add in the assembly\add* as a managerВҰ139997 working for \nd GodВҰ139996\nd* must have a clean record, not be self-centred, not be quick to get angry, not addicted to wine, not a bullyВҰ140005, and not greedyВҰ140007,
\v 8 butВҰ140008 rather hospitableВҰ140009, someone who loves what is goodВҰ140010, sensibleВҰ140011, honest, loves God, and self-controlled.
\v 9 He must hold faithfullyВҰ140020 to the message that was taughtВҰ140019, so that he will be effective in encouraging others with soundВҰ140034 teaching and to be rebukingВҰ140038 those who speakВҰ140037 againstВҰ140037 the message.
\s1 Handling those who go off the track
\p
\v 10 There's plenty of people who don't want to be told what to do, empty talkersВҰ140044 andВҰ140045 outright deceiversВҰ140046, especially those that push the letter of the law.
\v 11 These people need to be silencedВҰ140055 because they mess up wholeВҰ140057 families when they teachВҰ140060 them things that they shouldn'tВҰ140062вҖ”all for the sake of shamefulВҰ140065 game.
\v 12 One of theirВҰ140071 own prophetsВҰ140075 saidВҰ140068 that the people from CreteВҰ140076 are liarsВҰ140078, evilВҰ140079 beastsВҰ140080, and lazy gluttons,
\v 13 and that's right. For those reasons, you need to sternly tell them they're wrong, so that they can become soundВҰ140095 in their faithВҰ140098,
\v 14 andВҰ140103 not pay attention to Jewish mythsВҰ140102 or humanВҰ140105 rules which turn people away from the truthВҰ140108.
\v 15 For someone who's pure in their thinking, everything is pure to them, butВҰ140117 for unbelieversВҰ140118 and those who've strayed from the truth, nothingВҰ140119 is pure because their minds and consciencesВҰ140129 have already been damagedвҖ”
\v 16 they say that they know \nd GodВҰ140130\nd*, butВҰ140139 theirВҰ140133 actions show that they don't, and so they're detestableВҰ140137. They can no longer accept teaching so they're unsuitable for any goodВҰ140145 workВҰ140144.
\c 2
\s1 Proper behaviour for believers
