\p
\v 1 But youВҰ140147, \add Titos,\add* only \add вүҲteachВҰ140155 what's consistent with soundВҰ140154 doctrine\add*.
\v 2 Older menВҰ140156 should be soberВҰ140157, dignifiedВҰ140159, sensibleВҰ140160, and soundВҰ140161 in their faithВҰ140163, their loveВҰ140165, and their enduranceВҰ140167.
\v 3 Likewise olderВҰ140168 womenВҰ140168 should honour god by their behaviourВҰ140171, not making false accusations, not addicted to a lot of wine. They should teachВҰ140181 what is goodВҰ140181
\v 4 so that theyВҰ140184 can train the younger womenВҰ140186 to love their husbandsВҰ140187 and childrenВҰ140189,
\v 5 and to be sensibleВҰ140190 and pure, homemakersВҰ140192 that do goodВҰ140193 for others, living under the authority of theirВҰ140196 husbandsВҰ140198 so that others don'tВҰ140200 speak evil of God's messageВҰ140202 because of them.
\p
\v 6 Also encourage youngerВҰ140210 menВҰ140210 to be sensibleВҰ140213.
\v 7 Be a goodВҰ140220 exampleВҰ140219 in everything you do and in your teachingВҰ140224. Don't be led astray, maintain your dignityВҰ140229,
\v 8 watch every word that comes out of your lips, stay above reproachвҖ”all this so that those who oppose us can be reached because there's nothingВҰ140239 badВҰ140247 they can say about us.
\p
\v 9 SlavesВҰ140248 need to conform to their master's commands, aiming to pleaseВҰ140255. They shouldn'tВҰ140257 speakВҰ140258 againstВҰ140258 their mastersВҰ140250
\v 10 or be pilfering from them, rather theyВҰ140276 should displayВҰ140265 their goodВҰ140266 faithВҰ140264 so thatВҰ140270 their actions add to the teachingsВҰ140269 of \nd GodВҰ140275\nd* ourВҰ140274 saviourВҰ140272.
